name: CEC Pog LE #1
description: An extremely low effort memorialization of the moment that a mascot for a children's restaurant and entertainment company (est. 1977) used an online streaming service (est. 2011) to utter the word "poggers", likely one of the only times said puppet mascot has spoken on camera during streams. Although I personally believe this moment to hold cultural significance (old corporate mascot using modern platform and lingo), it may not, but I still wanted to explore this moment artistically, starting with lowest effort and gradually working towards the limits of my ability and patience.
